An official from the Tajik security ministry was  killed in an attack in a central town of the ex-Soviet republic, the Interfax  news agency reported Thursday.
Colonel Guravli Kadirov, 42, was killed by automatic gunfire at his  father's house in the town of Garm, on Wednesday evening, the agency said  quoting ministry sources.
The killers escaped after the attack, it said, giving no further details.  Authorities have launched an investigation.
